
bind() Function
---------------
The bind method is used to create a new function that, when invoked has a specified this value and optional arguements.

Syntax:
-------

function.bind(thisArg, arg1, arg2, ...)

*create a new funciton


Example
------
const person = {
    fullName: function ( location, rollNo) {
        return `${this.firstName} ${this.lastName} from ${location}, RollNo ${rollNo}`
    }
};

const person1 = {
    firstName: "Arjun",
    lastName: "Doss"
};

const person2 = {
    firstName: "Kamal",
    lastName: "Hassan"
};


//Bind | Returns Functions
let result1 = person.fullName.bind(person1, ["Bangalore", 34]) 
console.log(result1) // Arjun Doss from Bangalore, RollNO 34

let result2 = person.fullName.bind(person2, ["Chennai", 30]) 
console.log(result2) // Kamal Hassan from Chennai, RollNo 30


